      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was looking at the street maps of dc last night and something just clicked. like, it's not just random planning. when u look at the way the main avenues intersect with the monuments, it's not a grid. it's a pattern. almost like a sigil or a seal. have u ever looked at the geometry of the city layout from a non-standard perspective?",
